Background:

APIs like Yelp that 


Usage:

Yelp:

(see http://www.yelp.com/developers/documentation/search_api)

<form id="restaurant-locator" action="http://api.yelp.com/business_review_search?callback=?"> 
    <input type="text" id="location" name="location" />
    <input type="hidden" name="ywsid" value="Ky-PybyihkKCWAxEBeorYg" />
    <input type="hidden" id="category" name="category" value="restaurants" />
    <input type="hidden" id="drop" name="drop" value="lunch-location-drop" />
    <input type="submit" />
</form>


Flickr:

(from http://docs.jquery.com/Ajax/jQuery.getJSON#urldatacallback)

<form id="picture-search" action="http://api.flickr.com/services/feeds/photos_public.gne?jsoncallback=?"> 
    <input type="text" name="tags" value="cats" />
    <input type="hidden" name="tagmode" value="any" />
    <input type="hidden" name="format" value="json" />
    <input type="submit" />
</form>


Twitter:

Twitter doesn't use paramaters for all selection fields so directly calling the API for JSONP with $.getJSON is the preferred option.

http://jquery-howto.blogspot.com/2009/04/jquery-twitter-api-plugin.html



